:''This article is about the phrase; for the album by the Cranberries, see [[Bury the Hatchet (album)]].''

'''Bury the Hatchet''' is an [[American English]] [[colloquialism]] meaning "to make peace."  The phrase is an allusion to the figurative or literal practice of putting away the [[tomahawk]] at the cessation of hostilities among or by [[Native Americans]] in the Eastern United States, specifically the [[Iroquois]] confederacy.

